@startuml Integrita_Cascata

title Verifica Integrita DIP - Cascata Gerarchica e Aggregazione
top to bottom direction

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 12
}

legend left
Flusso di verifica:
1) Verifica hash solo sui File
2) Aggregazione verso l alto su ogni livello
3) Persistenza stato a ogni livello nello stesso scope transazionale
endlegend

frame "Transazione unica (BEGIN IMMEDIATE -> COMMIT | ROLLBACK)" {
  rectangle "DIP" as Dip #EAF7FF
  rectangle "DocumentClass" as DocClass #EAF7FF
  rectangle "Process" as Process #EAF7FF
  rectangle "Document" as Document #EAF7FF
  rectangle "File" as File #EAF7FF

  rectangle "HashingService\nSHA256(file) vs hash atteso" as Hash #FFF4DD
  database "SQLite\nintegrity_status" as Db #F6F6F6

  Dip -down-> DocClass : contiene 0..*
  DocClass -down-> Process : contiene 0..*
  Process -down-> Document : contiene 0..*
  Document -down-> File : contiene 0..*

  File --> Hash : checkFileIntegrity(path, hash)
  Hash --> File : VALID | INVALID | UNKNOWN

  File -up-> Document : aggregateStatuses(file[])
  Document -up-> Process : aggregateStatuses(document[])
  Process -up-> DocClass : aggregateStatuses(process[])
  DocClass -up-> Dip : aggregateStatuses(class[])

  File ..> Db : update file.integrity_status
  Document ..> Db : update document.integrity_status
  Process ..> Db : update process.integrity_status
  DocClass ..> Db : update document_class.integrity_status
  Dip ..> Db : update dip.integrity_status
}

note right of Dip
Regola aggregazione (ordine priorita):
1. Se esiste INVALID -> INVALID
2. Altrimenti se esiste UNKNOWN -> UNKNOWN
3. Altrimenti -> VALID
4. Lista figli vuota -> VALID
end note

@enduml
